Giordano's Pizza has made it possible to order the famous stuffed Chicago style pizza online and delivered to you any where in America.

formattedAddress: 3411 N Broadway St (at W Roscoe St)

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Milt’s mission is to nourish both the body and the mind, and to support community and conversation.

items.text: If you're on the lookout for Kosher barbecue, this is probably the only choice in town. But everyone will appreciate the Milt dog, which uses an all-beef Kosher hot dog.
Fried Okra
A great BBQ joint, Smoked Wings (while not huge), and Fried Okra are both great and well worth the prices, a very unique place!
Great kosher BBQ - don't expect any pork or dairy products here, you won't find them! In general it's more expensive b/c kosher meat is more expensive, but all profits go to charity!
$45 for a slab of ribs????? They are out of their minds. Go to Smoque.
Amazing food! We shared brisket and ribs sandwiches as well as Milt's dog. Everything was delicious.
Super yummy all Kosher restaurant. So many good things to eat.
All good! Especially the pulled chicken.
Kosher food at it's finest! Amazing!
Cornbread and Brisket Sandwich were on point. Skip the tomato base bbq sauce in favor of the mustard and enjoy kosher BBQ!
Deserts are terrible (yes all of them), smoked chicken and okra are amazing!
Braised short ribs are to die for!
Loved the smoked wings, but ribs were a bit bland and possibly burnt
Very loud, screaming children.
Food was good, try the blood orange margaritas
Best chili around!
Get the ribs and the beans.

Don't have pulled pork...

pageInfo.description: O'Hare International Airport is located 18 miles northwest of downtown Chicago.  It's core mission is to provide outstanding service and amenities to customers.

items.text: "When checking a bag, I always make sure to pack a CONAN intern - that way, if my bags get lost, and they're still alive, they can call and tell me where they are." - Conan O'Brien
Fly somewhere
Check out the rotating toilet seat covers!
Check out the sick light show on the way to Concourse C!! :)
If you are on a moving sidwalk and don't feel like walking please stay to the right. The rest of us are trying to get by lol
Take the blue line. It's less stressful than driving.
Don't worry, you'll make your connection. It's delayed too.

Top Dining Options: Tortas Frontera, Garrett Popcorn, & Wolfgang Puck Cafe in Terminals 1/3; Wicker Park Sushi Bar, Terminal 2; America's Dog & Berghoff Café, Terminal 1; La Tapenade in Terminals 1/2.
This water bottle refill station / water fountain saved over ten thousand bottles from entering landfill and counting!
ORD stands for the airport's old name - Orchard Fields.

On a layover? Head over to the United Airlines terminal to take in the neon lit pedestrian bridge & dinosaur. If you've got a little extra time, head over to the WWII era plane & get a history lesson!
Wow! The fuel tank capacity of a Boeing 747-8 is 242k litres, about 4000 times more than an average car!
best people watching in the world.
Use a mobile boarding pass! Way easier and save paper
You can't be in Chicago without trying Garrett Popcorn. Located in terminal B near security. Get the Chicago mix for a sweet/savory treat that eases the pain of the inevitable delays at this airport.
Tortas Frontera, in Terminals 1 and 3, is an outpost of Chicago’s best Mexican restaurant, Frontera Grill. Order a fresh-shaken margarita and one of chef Rick Bayless’s griddle-baked tortas.
On the bright side, the wait to board is still shorter than your average DMV visit. #DontBlowIt
The automated toilet seat cover is great!
Bring Xanax, you'll need it
Some of the most creative and well placed advertising of recent years has happened here. Favorite? Security trays advertising Amtrack reminding that THEY let you keep your shoes on!

venue.name: Nookies Too Restaurant

formattedAddress: 2114 N Halsted St (btwn Webster & Dickens Ave)

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Nookies is a casual, American restaurant which cooks fresh, no-nonsense, wholesome food and serves it in a friendly, efficient, unpretentious, casual-but-correct manner. It is first and foremost, a neighborhood place.

items.text: The fall special trio is delicious. Way too much food for one person to handle, but delicious.
Nookies is BYOB, bring champagne to make mimosas!
The Paris Benedict is delish! Gruyure cheese poached eggs, cherry bacon, truffle chive cream...MMMM!!!
If you're a fan of biscuits and gravy, there's is great!  Try it!
Two words: Blueberry Pancakes.
Great brunch!! I always look at the special or ask the waiter for recommendations. Love their savory dishes
Coffee, French toast
Fairly priced for the portions and hugh quality. Highly recommended great for any occasion, kids, dates, casual brunch.
If you like burgers and you like Acapulco, try the Acapulco Burger - it's loaded with fresh avocado.
Croissant French toast napolean is to die for. Offered in the spring only. Womens bathroom does not lock. Go pee somewhere else.
Great casual brunch spot. Lots of interesting dishes beyond the basics.
Huevos rancheros are delicious!
Lucky for us, Nookies has a second outpost, appropriately named Nookies, Too. There, you’ll find all the corned beef hash and crunchy French toast of the other Nookies without the wait.
Come early on the weekends...there WILL be a wait!
Fabulous cup of coffee. Exceptional service.
...very yummy
The Dixie Benedict was crazy good, and not as heavy as you'd think. The croissant French toast Napoleon was just way too dense. I like croissants because they're light and fluffy. This was a brick.
Coffee, French toast, and corn need hash.
Just like everyone else says, the Dixie Eggs Benedict are to die for. Gooey sausage gravy, moist buttered biscuits, nice slab of ham plus eggs. Comes with hash browns, which mix well with gravy.
Trendy, nice location, brief wait on Father's Day, but reasonable. Great portions for the price. And high quality of food. The Nutella banana crepes were amazing!

items.text: 1 hour wait turned to 2+ hours for a party of four. Manager Seth unfriendly and unwilling to simply combine two-tops to four-tops to best accommodate parties. Will not come back. Missing Countner!!!
Don't complain about the line, these are some of the top burgers in the city. Good things come to those who wait.
Kuma's Corner polished for the Lincoln Park crowd. Same great food, but not nearly the charm (read grit) of the original.
Don't know what people keep bitching about but this place was great, the staff was awesomely sweet, food was AMAZING!!! And the music was killer. Great place totally coming back!
Eat at the bar, even if tables are open. Great experience, bartenders a super knowledgable about burgers and the fantastic beer selection!
2+ hour wait. Rude staff. Poor crowd management. Music just adds to the rage.
Probably the best burger I've had in Chicago and the fries are amazing
If you love the Original Kuma's you will hate this location! Unless you want to hang out with Yuppies or maybe throw your Grandma a surprise bday party or maybe have your book club meeting! Lame!
Bathrooms are way in the back past the bondage sketches
Pretentious level at toxic level... I love Kuma's and that it's closer to home; but the fucking Lakeview crowd makes me want to curb stomp some faces.
They only accept ONE credit card per table. LAME!
Don't let the relatively low rating fool you. This is one of the best burgers in Chicago.
Agree? Don't come here.
Courtney was our server & was knowledgeable when it came to what beer was best with what burger. Ten minute wait & we were seated even less than that. The bus boys are sweethearts! Same great food.
Not too bad a wait afterwork, but started gaining a crowd around 6...great burgers of course!!!
Waited only 30min,  burger was amazing, staff was super accommodating!
The Plague Bringer is good, but they are not messing around with the garlic. It is definitely present.
Try the Slayer burger!
Burgers are overrated. The patty itself is flavorless, but, damn, they've got good ketchup!!!
Calamari is back!
